==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Labor Day
<hw>Labor Day</hw>. <def>In most of the States and Territories of the
United States, a day, usually the first Monday of September, set aside
as a legal holiday, in honor of, or in the interest of, workingmen as a
class. Also, a similar holiday in Canada, Australia, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Labored</ent>⟦br⟧
